text.tspan: Shunned by her tribe since birth, Aloy has never
known a mother’s embrace or the acceptance of a
community. Her only companion was Rost, the
stern, impassive recluse who fostered her.
Rost taught Aloy to survive any physical hardship
and to scorn comforts as weakness – but he
couldn’t provide the answer to the questions which
troubled her above all else: who her parents were,
and why she was cast out.
